#Text=I think this is a very important issue and I will do everything I can to draw attention to it !
#Text=You were one of the public faces of the Orange Revolution , and ended up becoming a member of Parliament for a while .
#Text=What caused you to throw your support behind Viktor Yushchenko so publicly , considering it could have been dangerous not only to your career , but your life ?
#Text=It seems that staying in the Verkhovna Rada [ Editor 's note : The Parliament of the Ukraine ] may [ be able to solve ] certain problems .
#Text=Unfortunately , not always .
#Text=I realized that in our country , if you want to do something for your Motherland – you should do it by yourself ; not hoping that one day somebody will hear or help you ...
#Text=When you left Parliament , you said , " I still hope for real changes and for a new political generation to come with the mentality to work and not being corrupt . "
#Text=What did you mean by that ?
#Text=All that I can say is that I 'm not in policy any more .
#Text=And I 'm very happy because of that !
#Text=It seemed to me that [ passing policies ] could help me make more for my country , but on the contrary , [ policy ] just tied my hands .
#Text=I came into politics [ with ] " [ rose-colored ] glasses " and [ left ] there very disappointed ...
#Text=When I was asking for research help among the Ukrainian and Russian-speaking Wikipedians , one of the Russians made an off-hand comment to me that stuck .
#Text=" Ukraine is just a part of Russia anyway . "
#Text=When I asked a Ukrainian Wikipedian what that meant to him , he said it upset him .
#Text=How do you feel when you encounter such attitudes , considering you also release your music to the Russian market ?
#Text=Ukraine is [ an ] absolutely independent country , with her own culture , language , [ and ] history .
#Text=After winning on the Eurovision I [ received ] a lot of invitations [ to ] Russia .
#Text=Many friends of mine live there .
#Text=My grandparents live in Yekaterinburg .
#Text=I had a lot of propositions to make a big tour in Russia .
#Text=I like to give concerts there .
#Text=We will definitely show Russia my new Wild Energy show .
#Text=Counterpoint on the East in Eurovision

#Text=One final political question , and this one relates to Eurovision : I interviewed past winners Nicole and Anne Marie David , and both seemed to indicate that " bloc voting " could exist amongst nations ; in Nicole 's case , she believed it is currently occurring , especially between the countries of Eastern Europe .
#Text=Your song received votes from nearly every country in Europe , but other winners were n't so fortunate , like the song from Russia last year .
#Text=Do you believe " bloc voting " exists between the countries of Eastern Europe , and do you feel it is unfair to Western European performers who enter the Contest ?
